            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-11-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-11-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="20" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d20">
                <head>No. 20.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Baron <persName type="from">Schaeffer</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Frelinghuysen</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-11-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 21,
                                    1883</date>. (Received November 22.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your letter dated 13th instant, with respect to the
                            unfortunate affairs of the two Hungarian ships, Mimi P. and Ararat, in
                            Philadelphia.</p>
                <p>I cannot but express my sincerest thanks for the compliance with my
                            request by which you enable me to give to my Government a detailed
                            reply, so urgently asked for by them.</p>
                <p>Accept, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>SCHAEFFER.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
